Package sample.start

Class StartMeUp

java.lang.Object
sample.start.StartMeUp
public class StartMeUp
extends java.lang.Object
The startMeUp class is the game engine of this game. All methods related to the game engine in Model are defined here.

    • HandleKey

      public void HandleKey​(javafx.scene.input.KeyCode code)
      This method checks the keyboard input and calls move() method accordingly. It also set the direction of the keeper when moving, which use a static int variable to represent the direction.
      Parameters:
      code - keyCode code.

    • GetKeeper

      This method gets the index stand for the direction of the keeper.

    • antiPoint

      private java.awt.Point antiPoint​(java.awt.Point delta)
      This method input a Point delta and output the opposite point of this point.
      Parameters:
      delta - Point delta which stands for up, right, down and left.
      Returns:
      antiPoint which is the the opposite point of input.

    • move

      private void move​(java.awt.Point delta)
      This method first checks whether the game is complete, if it is, return. Otherwise, it moves the objects according to the target object of the keeper.
      Parameters:
      delta - The direction to move to.

    • LoadGameFile

      public java.util.List<Level> LoadGameFile​(java.io.InputStream input)
      This method reads the game from the input file. and save levels in a arrayList. It also initialize movesCount, timeLoad, mapSetName and levelName.
      Parameters:
      input - the file's inputStream.
      Returns:
      an arrayList contains levels.

    • GetNextLevel

      public Level GetNextLevel()
      This method gets the next level of the current level. If the current level is null, it returns the first level, else if the current level is the last level, it returns null. Otherwise, it returns the next level.
      Returns:
      next level if it has, otherwise null.

    • GetCurrentLevel

      public Level GetCurrentLevel()
      This methods gets the current level.
      Returns:
      Level currentLevel.

    • GetLevelIndex

      public int GetLevelIndex()
      This method gets the index of the current level. When the current level is completed, it returns current level index - 1 since the current level is actually next level now. If the saved game is loaded, it returns the saved level index.
      Returns:
      the index of the current level.

    • ToggleDebug

      public void ToggleDebug()
      This method set the debug state to the opposite state.

    • SaveGame

      public java.lang.String SaveGame()
      This method get the current level state and convert it to String.
      Returns:
      String representing levels.

    • Undo

      public int Undo()
      This method is used to undo the step. It moves the keeper and the crate to the previous point. If undo failed, it returns 0 then the prompt will be displayed by SubModel.Undo.
      Returns:
      int representing undo success or not.

    • ResetLevel

      public void ResetLevel()
      This method is used to reset the level. It moves the keeper and crates to their initial point.
